createVector.!doc: Creates a new p5.Vector (the datatype for storing vectors).

p5.Vector.!type: fn(x: number, y: number, z: number)

toString.!doc: Returns a string representation of a vector v by calling String(v) or v.toString(). This method is useful for logging vectors in the console.

copy.!doc: Gets a copy of the vector, returns a p5.Vector object.

p5.Vector.!doc: A class to describe a two or three dimensional vector, specifically a Euclidean (also known as geometric) vector.
